BCD multiplication involves scaling one decimal number by another. 
This project sought to design and implement a four-digit BCD multiplier core with similarity investigation on the Spartan-6 XC6LX16-CS324 FPGA. 
The design was also required to validate inputs avoiding invalid BCD digits and trivial multiplications by ones and zeros. 
Multiplication was based on parallel partial product generation by the accumulation of a sequentially shifted multiplicand. 
The design was implemented on Xilinx ISE 14.7. It was then simulated on ISim and validated on the Digilent Nexy3 toolkit.
